column4: 1. Switch to underground mode. Use the icon right beside the dollar note.
2. Use the + (plus) key to go one level up. Use the - (minus) key to go one level down.
3. In underground mode, you can only use the tunnel tools to build a street or a rail track.
4. Build stations or yards as usual.
5. To continue a road or a track on a higher or on a lower level, use the slope tools to push the track down or up. Then change to the upper or lower level and connect with the tunnel tool.
6. You always have to start a tunnel on a slope from outside.  If you want to build a tunnel entrance only, keep the CTRL key pressed and click with the tunnel tool active.
